        <header>
          <h1>Hi, I'm <br>Kade Illian</h1>
          <p>A Ruby on Rails Developer Based out of Bozeman, MT</p>
        </header>
        <p>I became interested in computer science during my freshman year of high school and competed at the
          district level in an academic Java competition. Throughout high school, my love of problem solving and working inside of a team grew.  Whether it was being a lead server at Cracker Barrel or creating a widely successful student section for our football team, I loved figuring out how to motivate people to become as passionate as I was about the task at hand.  After moving to Montana with the intention of taking a gap year before attending college, I realized that my passion lay within the wide world of web development.  In March of 2022, I began to teach myself basic HTML and CSS. Then in July of 2022, I took the first major step toward my career in web development: attending Actualize Bootcamp.  Here, I learned the basics of Ruby on Rails, JavaScript, React.js, SQL, Git, Github, and more.  With this newly aquired knowledge, I have been able to create <a href="">projects</a> such as this website.  My career as a web developer is only just beginning, but I hope to show you some of what I have learned through this site!</p>
