      <div class="features">
        <article>
          <span class="icon fa-gem"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>Ruby</h3>
            <p>Ruby is an OOP language developed by Yukihiro Matsumoto.  This is the first language that Actualize introduces to its students because of its english-like syntax and its strong reliance upon object oriented programming.  Ruby pairs with the Rails framework, allowing developers the ability to create powerful web applications.  I have used Ruby in conjunction with Rails, to build a to-do list appliation, to create web-scrappers, and much more.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="icon solid fa-train"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>Rails</h3>
            <p>Rails is a Ruby based framework that allows developers to easily create full-stack websites.  Rails is based on the concept of "convention over configuration", meaning that a developer should utilize Rails in the way that it was designed to be used.  This was one of my biggest challenges while creating this website, but once you understand this fundamental concept, Rails becomes an immensly powerful framework, allowing you to deploy fully functioning RESTful websites in a relatively short amount of time.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="icon brands fa-js"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>JavaScript</h3>
            <p>JavaScript is the world's most popular programming language in 2022.  JavaScript gives developers access to cookies, dynamic web pages, user input, and many more fluid web elements.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="icon brands fa-react"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>React</h3>
            <p>React is a JavaScript framework that allows developers to create "single-page web applications".  As web applications continue to move towards the single-page model, React gains more and more popularity.  In 2022 it is widely considered to be the most widely used JavaScript framework.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="icon brands fa-html5"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>HTML/CSS</h3>
            <p>HTML is the language that gives structure to web pages today.  In Rails, embedded Ruby is converted into HTML before it is displayed to the user on the front-end.  HTML on its own can be fairly bland and uninteresting for the modern internet user.  This is where CSS comes in as a styling language to gives us the colors, margins, image stylings, and much, much more.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
        <article>
          <span class="icon brands fa-git"></span>
          <div class="content">
            <h3>Git</h3>
            <p>Git is a version control system that is widely used in the web development world today.  Writing thoughtful, concise Git messages is an essential part of working on the modern software team.  By effectively communicating what you have changed in the code base through your commit messages, a developer can help his coworkers and his or herself by being able to pinpoint where a bug may have been introduced into the application.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
